  "time_ut": 1662286059,
  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0baa\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bc1 \u0ba8\u0bcb\u0baf\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbe\u0ba9 \u0bae\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b95\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Acute shortage of medicines for cancer patients",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "It is reported that there has been a shortage of 20 types of drugs used for cancer patients, including the tabzumab vaccine given to breast cancer patients, and their continuous treatments have been stopped.",
        "According to the Ministry of Health sources, there is a shortage of drugs including tabzumab vaccine in many hospitals including the general hospitals of Colombo, Kandy, Karapitiya and Jaffna and Maharagama Apeksha Hospital.",
        "The hospital management has informed the Ministry of Health that about 500 vaccines have been procured and distributed to the hospitals despite the purchase permission to procure 1000 breast cancer vaccines.",
        "It is reported that patient care services have completely collapsed due to the lack of these drugs despite the need for continuous treatment of cancer patients.",
        "According to Health Ministry sources, about 3,000 cancer patients come for treatment at Maharagama Hospital every year and about 1,000 patients are treated daily as inpatients and outpatients."
      ],
